  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p>We've handpicked these cabins for their unique charm and furnishings. Scattered in the grounds surrounding the Ylläsrinne Hotel, they range from 150 to 1000 metres away from the hotel. Each property is equipped with Wi-Fi and firewood is provided as standard. </p>
<p>As a minimum, all cabins provide kitchen facilities with fridge, oven, microwave, kettle and toaster. They all have a sauna to warm up in after exploring the great outdoors, plus bed linen and towels are included (beds to be made on arrival). </p>
<p>Please note that the steps to the mezzanines are steep and mezzanine ceilings are low or sloping.</p>
<p><strong>Karpalo </strong>sleeps 2-5 people and is about 44m². This cabin has one twin bedroom, plus one single and one double bed on the mezzanine. There is one bathroom WC with shower.<strong> </strong>This cabin is semi detached and located 500 metres from the Ylläsrinne Hotel.</p>
<p><img src="/media/13091640/karpalo-838x350.jpg" alt="Karpalo Cabin Lapland" data-udi="umb://media/f3905eaf1a064ab99bc24a1e2859055c" /></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Villa Ylläs A </strong><strong>&amp; B </strong>sleep 2-6 people and are about 55m². Villa Ylläs A has two twin bedrooms, Villa Ylläs B has one double bedroom and one twin bedroom and both cabins have two single beds in the mezzanine (suitable for children aged 8-14 years only). There is one bathroom WC with shower.<strong> </strong>These cabins are semi-detached and sit side by side, located about 500 metres from the Ylläsrinne Hotel.</p>
<p><img src="/media/13091641/suppapolku-838x350.jpg" alt="Suppapolku Cabin Lapland" data-udi="umb://media/44abdf229a064ef381693cd8e5ad0128" /></p>
<p> </p>]]></roomsDescription>
